                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;You should not use the &quot;stock&quot; OpenSSL settings like that. That&apos;s because you cannot place DNS names in the Subject Alternate Name (SAN). You need to provide a configuration file with an &lt;code&gt;alternate_names&lt;/code&gt; section and pass it with the &lt;code&gt;-config&lt;/code&gt; option. Also, placing a DNS name in the Common Name (CN) is deprecated (but not prohibited) by both the IETF and the CA/Browser Forums. Any DNS name in the CN must also be present in the SAN. There&apos;s no way to avoid using the SAN. See answer below.&lt;/span&gt;

